item.title: [+964] WTF? RIAA Claims Music Pirates Hurt Haiti Fund Raising!
item.description: Wow. The RIAA is getting seriously desperate these days. Now the RIAA is claiming that P2P file sharers are "undermining" humanitarian efforts in Haiti. Now that's quite a claim, and you would think the RIAA would have some evidence to back it up, but (of course), it doesn't. It's just making stuff up.

item.title: [+923] Saddam Hussein's Destroyed & Recycled Palaces (PICS)
item.description: Photographer Richard Mosse traveled to Iraq to document this bizarre circumstance, this juxtaposition of supposed liberators dwelling in the very home of the dictator they vowed to depose. He called the resulting book Breach, a nod to the liberators stepping into the breach they created when Hussein was removed from power.

item.title: [+556] Dark, dangerous asteroids found lurking near Earth
item.description: An infrared space telescope has spotted several very dark asteroids that have been lurking unseen near Earth's orbit. Their obscurity have kept them hidden from surveys designed to detect things that might hit our planet.

item.title: [+515] From two-trillion-degree heat, researchers create new matter
item.description: A worldwide team of researchers have for the first time created a particle that is believed to have been in existence immediately after the creation of the universe - the so-called 'Big Bang'.
